# {{.ProjectName}}

Cursor workspace-config scaffold generated by [plugin-kit-ai](https://github.com/777genius/plugin-kit-ai) `init`.

This lane models the documented Cursor workspace subset that fits the package-standard authoring model today.

## Status

- Target lane: `cursor`
- Platform family: `code_plugin`
- Launcher: not used
- Runtime claim: config/workspace lane only

## First Run

```bash
plugin-kit-ai generate .
plugin-kit-ai generate --check .
plugin-kit-ai validate . --platform cursor --strict
```

## Target Files

- `src/targets/cursor/rules/`: Cursor `.mdc` rules mirrored into `.cursor/rules/`
- `src/mcp/servers.yaml`: canonical portable MCP authored source; `plugin-kit-ai init --extras` pre-seeds a starter and generate projects it into `.cursor/mcp.json`
- root `CLAUDE.md` and `AGENTS.md`: boundary docs that tell humans and agents to edit only `src/`
- `.cursor/mcp.json`: generated managed Cursor MCP config
- `.cursor/rules/`: generated managed Cursor rules

## Current Boundary

- Supported in v1: `.cursor/mcp.json` and project-root `.cursor/rules/**`
- Deferred in v1: root `CLAUDE.md`, global `~/.cursor/mcp.json`, nested non-root `.cursor/rules/**`, and any VS Code extension packaging lane
- Root `AGENTS.md` is reserved for plugin-root boundary instructions and is not a Cursor-native authored surface
